      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even if you felt fine before, that doesn't mean the interaction isn't happening internally. The interference is biochemical, not just about a direct \"contact\" at the same moment. Spacing them out by a few hours is a better strategy than drinking them together, but for absolute certainty and to avoid any risk, you should always clear this with your prescribing physician. They know your full medical profile and can give you the most precise guidance.",
